22/09/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The police chiefs and other senior security officials from BiH, Albania, Croatia, Macedonia, Montenegro, Serbia and UNMIK met in Sarajevo on Thursday (21 September) to discuss progress achieved in implementing the regional strategy for fighting organised crime and corruption, approved by regional interior ministers a year ago. 
BiH representative Srdan Vranic, co-ordinator of the CARDS programme, told participants that his country has made some major achievements, and has drafted its own strategy to combat organised crime and corruption. 
(NTV Hayat - 21/09/06)
